    • Constructor Detail

      • DualCounterExampleElement

        public DualCounterExampleElement(String name,
                                 String comment,
                                 URI location,
                                 ProductDESProxy des,
                                 Collection<? extends AutomatonProxy> automata,
                                 TraceProxy trace1,
                                 TraceProxy trace2)
        Creates a new dual counterexample.
        Parameters:
        name - The name to be given to the new counterexample.
        comment - A comment describing the new counterexample, or null.
        location - The URI to be associated with the new document, or null.
        des - The product DES for which this counterexample is generated.
        automata - The set of automata for the new counterexample, or null if empty.
        trace1 - The first of the two traces that define the dual counterexample.
        trace2 - The second of the two traces that define the dual counterexample.
        Throws:
        ItemNotFoundException - to indicate that one of the given automata, events, or states cannot be found in the product DES.
